The Knight in Rusty Armor (Robert Fisher)
- Your Highlight on page 30 | location 449-453 | Added on Friday, 14 September 2018 22:37:13

In order to pass the time, the knight began talking aloud to himself. He said anything that came into his mind. He talked about what he was like as a little boy and how he was different from the other boys he knew. While they hunted quail and played “Pin the Tail on the Boar,” he sat inside and read. Since books were handwritten by the monks then, they were few, and he had soon read them all. That is when he began talking eagerly to anyone who passed his way. When there was no one to talk to, he talked to himself-just as he was doing now. He unexpectedly found himself saying that he had talked so much all his life to keep himself from feeling alone.
