The Solution to Social Anxiety: Break Free From the Shyness That Holds You Back (Aziz Gazipura)
- Your Highlight on page 89 | location 1351-1354 | Added on Tuesday, 29 March 2022 18:20:59

Sharing what you want is a key aspect of social confidence. It is essential to start sharing what you want, even when you are unsure if the other person wants the same thing. Many people will wait to find out what the other person wants, then determine if they should say what they want. When we do this, we are operating from the following belief: If they want what I want, then my want is allowed. If they do not, then my want is wrong or selfish, and I must hide it.
